Parliament, Monday, 21 October 2019 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa), will tomorrow be briefed by the Inter-Ministerial Task Team on the defaulting municipalities that are owing Eskom
	
	Details are as follows:
	Date: Tuesday, 22 October 2019
	Time: 09h30
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building.
	
	Meanwhile, the Portfolio Committee on Environment, Forestry and Fisheries will tomorrow be briefed by NGOs on the update on the state of captive lion breeding in South Africa and the economics thereof.
	
	Details are as follows:
	Date: Tuesday, 22 October 2019
	Time: 10h00
	Venue: Committee Room S12A, Ground Floor, NCOP Building.
	
